<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468409>
    dc:description "FIGURE 13A–D. Patrera bonaldoi n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-9661): A habitus, C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view. Female (AMNH): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view; G epigynum, dorsal view. Abbreviations: BE, base of the embolus; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; H, hood; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum; VTP, ventral tegular process. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B: 3.5mm; C: 1mm; D–E: 0.5mm; F–G: 0.25mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4468409/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468453>
    dc:description "FIGURE 32. Distribution of species of the florezi group in Colombia." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4468453/files/figure.png" ;
